# Description: Maximum working time per person.
# Scenario: One boat allows 12h operation (maxWorkingHours = 12). A1 (7h) and A2 (5h). Only one person P1 with required skills.
# Reasoning: The model assigns P1 to the boat and allows both tasks to be executed sequentially, totaling 12h.
# Since there is no constraint limiting individual working time per person, P1 can be assigned to the full duration.
# Expected result: WorkHours = 12.
# Note: With an additional (non-modelled) personal working time limit (e.g., 8h), only one task would be feasible.
# Maximize WorkHours: 7.
data;
set TASKS := A1 A2;
set QUALIS := Tech;
set PEOPLE := P1;
set TOOLS := W1;

param amountBoats := 1;
param maxWorkingHours := 12;

param duration := A1 7 A2 5;

param hasQuali := P1 Tech 1;
param requiredQualis := A1 Tech 1 A2 Tech 1;
param requiredTools := A1 W1 0 A2 W1 0;
param stockTools := W1 0;

end;
